1 forth in IC 35-50-1-2(c) through IC 35-50-1-2(d).
2 (k) (j) As used in this subsection, "family member" means a child,
3 grandchild, parent, grandparent, or spouse of the person. It is a defense
4 to a prosecution under subsection (b) that the person reasonably
5 believed that the person's family member:
6 (1) was in the marked off area; and
7 (2) had suffered bodily injury or was at risk of suffering bodily
8 injury;
9 if the person is not charged as a defendant in connection with the
10 offense, if applicable, that caused the area to be secured by barrier tape
11 or other physical barriers.
12 SECTION 2. An emergency is declared for this act.
